  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/3888",
  "title": "Dynamically change search config based on current refinements",
  "body": "**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe 🙏**\r\n\r\nIn our UI, when users select different categories, we want add/alter filters, optionalFilters and maybe other config attributes to the search.\r\n\r\nI understand that Query Rules can accomplish some of this.... I was hoping for another option at query time using Instantsearch.\r\n\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like 🤔**\r\n\r\nI would like to alter search config based on current refinements.   I tried nesting ais-config inside ais-current-refinements... hoping to use refinement items slot scope in ais-config... this doesn't work of course and I'm probably in fantasy land even trying.\r\n\r\n**Describe alternatives you've considered ✨**\r\n\r\nQuery Rules comes close...  It feels wrong, to put some filters in query rules and some in Instantsearch config... but I may be overthinking it.   I don't believe Query Rules can use query-time data in Consequences.... so maybe that's one reason to consider a different solution\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\n\r\nInstantsearch Docs say \"In order to dynamically update the search parameters, you should create a new custom widget.\"   ...so I'm not the only one considering this.\r\n",
